    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The red-coloured wood of the mahogany gum-tree (Eucalyptus marginata) of West Australia that is strong, hard, reasonably fire-resistant and rot resistant. Known to be used for flooring.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
